<paragraph id="C24C8F6DFFDFFF8855F814A7FCD3FF0F" blockId="2.[400,878,216,243]" box="[400,878,216,243]" pageId="2" pageNumber="497">
<heading id="99043801FFDFFF8855F814A7FCD3FF0F" bold="true" box="[400,878,216,243]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="2" pageNumber="497" reason="2">
<emphasis id="F087537FFFDFFF8855F814A7FCD3FF0F" bold="true" box="[400,878,216,243]" pageId="2" pageNumber="497">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="05F3F4EEFFDFFF88558314A7FCD3FF0F" authority="Hayashi, 2008" authorityName="Hayashi" authorityYear="2008" box="[491,878,216,243]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudohesperus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F087537FFFDFFF88558314A7FD12FF0E" bold="true" box="[491,687,216,243]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="497">Pseudohesperus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="A662F29CFFDFFF8856D214A7FCD3FF0F" author="HAYASHI" box="[698,878,216,242]" pageId="2" pageNumber="497" pagination="145 - 153" refId="ref10516" refString="HAYASHI, Y. 2008: Pseudohesperus, a new genus of Philonthina (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae) from East Asia, with redescription of its type species Philonthus rutiliventris Sharp. Entomological Review of Japan 63: 145 - 153." type="journal article" year="2008">Hayashi, 2008</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C24C8F6DFFDFFF8854DD156EFBB9FDF4" blockId="2.[151,1127,273,522]" pageId="2" pageNumber="497">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="05F3F4EEFFDFFF88554F156DFE69FED4" authorityName="Hayashi" authorityYear="2008" box="[295,468,274,297]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudohesperus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F087537FFFDFFF88554F156DFE69FED4" box="[295,468,274,297]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="497">Pseudohesperus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was characterized in great detail by 
<bibRefCitation id="A662F29CFFDFFF885738156DFC47FED4" author="HAYASHI" box="[848,1018,273,297]" pageId="2" pageNumber="497" pagination="145 - 153" refId="ref10516" refString="HAYASHI, Y. 2008: Pseudohesperus, a new genus of Philonthina (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae) from East Asia, with redescription of its type species Philonthus rutiliventris Sharp. Entomological Review of Japan 63: 145 - 153." type="journal article" year="2008">HAYASHI (2008)</bibRefCitation>
: the genus is closely allied to 
<taxonomicName id="05F3F4EEFFDFFF885535154DFDEEFEB4" authority="Stephens, 1829" authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1829" box="[349,595,305,329]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bisnius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F087537FFFDFFF885535154DFE11FEB4" box="[349,428,306,329]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="497">Bisnius</emphasis>
Stephens, 1829
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="05F3F4EEFFDFFF8856EE154DFC35FEB4" authority="Stephens, 1829" authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1829" box="[646,904,305,329]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Gabrius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F087537FFFDFFF8856EE154DFD60FEB4" box="[646,733,306,329]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="497">Gabrius</emphasis>
Stephens, 1829
</taxonomicName>
, because of the similar structure of protarsi, but is easily distinguishable from them by the following characters: (1) mesoventrite strongly convex medially in a subtriangular form, without a transverse carina; (2) male sternite 9 with a pair of long appendages and without any long erect bristles; (3) female second gonocoxite very slender and long; (4) chaetotaxy of the pronotum composed of only a pair of anterolateral macrosetae, basolateral setae absent; (5) gular sutures gradually convergent posteriad to the neck constriction, not parallel in posterior (basal) half.
</paragraph>
